9:
May those who live in the wilderness bow down before him;
\q may his enemies lick the dust.
\q

11:
Indeed, may all kings fall down before him;
\q may all nations serve him.
\q

16:
May there be abundance of grain in the land;
\q on the mountaintops may their crops wave.
\q May the fruit of it be like Lebanon;
\q may the people flourish in the cities like the grass of the field.

17:
May his name endure forever;
\q may his name continue as long as the sun;
\q may people be blessed in him;
\q may all nations call him blessed.
